<!May's first JavaScript Tutorial. Sep 2018>

<html>
	<head>
		<title> May </title>
	</head>

	<body>
		<h1> This is the beginning of JavaScript. </h1>
		<h4> The following examples are from 'https://www.w3schools.com/js/default.asp'.</h3>
		<h4> JavaScript is in the HTML body.</h3>

		<p id="demo"> JavaScript can change HTML content.</p>
		<button type = "button"
		onclick='document.getElementById("demo").innerHTML = "Hello from JavaScript"'>Click Me for Hello demo!</button>

		<p id="demo2"> JavaScript can change HTML attribute values. 
	  				 	In this case, JS will cahnge the value of src attribute of an image. </p>
		<button onclick="document.getElementById('myImage').src='https://www.w3schools.com/js/pic_bulbon.gif'">Turn on the light</button>
		<img id="myImage" src="https://www.w3schools.com/js/pic_bulboff.gif" style="width:100px">
		<button onclick="document.getElementById('myImage').src='https://www.w3schools.com/js/pic_bulboff.gif'">Turn off the light</button>


		<p id="demo3"> JavaScript can change HTML styles.</p>
		<button type="button" 
		onclick="document.getElementById('demo3').style.fontSize='35px'">Click Me to change HTML styles!</button>


		<p id="demo4"> JavaScript can hide HTML elements.</p>
		<button type="button"
		onclick="document.getElementById('demo4').style.display = 'none'">Click me to hide HTML elements.</button>


		<p> JavaScript can show hidden HTML elements.</p>
		<p id="demo5" style="display: none"> Hello JavaScript! </p>
		<button type = "button"
		onclick="document.getElementById('demo5').style.display='block'"> Click me to show hidden HTML elements! </button>
    
	</body>

</html>
